{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Open `https://git-scm.com/downloads` in your web browser. You should see download options for Windows, macOS, and Linux.",
      "title": "Open the Git Download Page"
    },
    {
      "text": "Click **Windows** and save the `.exe` file. The download may start automatically; when finished, the installer should appear in your Downloads folder.",
      "title": "Download Git for Windows"
    },
    {
      "text": "Open the downloaded `.exe` file. Approve the security prompt if one appears; the Git Setup window should open.",
      "title": "Launch the Windows Installer"
    },
    {
      "text": "Keep the recommended settings and click **Next** until **Install** appears. Then click **Install** and wait for the progress bar to finish.",
      "title": "Install Git on Windows"
    },
    {
      "text": "Click **Finish** when setup completes. If available, leave **Launch Git Bash** selected; a terminal window should open.",
      "title": "Finish Windows Setup"
    },
    {
      "text": "On macOS, open **Terminal**, type `xcode-select --install`, and press Return. A software installation prompt should appear.",
      "title": "Request Git on macOS"
    },
    {
      "text": "Click **Install** in the macOS prompt, accept the license, and wait for installation to finish. You should see a completion message.",
      "title": "Install Git on macOS"
    },
    {
      "text": "On Ubuntu or Debian Linux, open Terminal and run `sudo apt update`. Enter your password if prompted; package information should finish updating without errors.",
      "title": "Update Linux Packages"
    },
    {
      "text": "Run `sudo apt install git` and type `Y` if prompted. On Fedora, use `sudo dnf install git` instead. Wait until the terminal prompt returns.",
      "title": "Install Git on Linux"
    },
    {
      "text": "Open a new Terminal or Git Bash window, run `git --version`, and press Enter. Success is confirmed when you see output such as `git version 2.x.x`.",
      "title": "Verify the Installation"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Turn on the hazard warning lights. Confirm both dashboard indicators flash; if the vehicle is exposed to traffic or the location feels unsafe, stay clear of traffic and call roadside assistance.",
      "title": "Turn On the Hazard Lights"
    },
    {
      "text": "Park on firm, level ground away from moving traffic. Avoid hills, soft soil, and narrow shoulders. Confirm the vehicle is stable and has enough working space around the flat tire.",
      "title": "Park on Level Ground"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press the parking brake pedal or pull the parking brake lever fully. Confirm the parking-brake warning light appears on the dashboard.",
      "title": "Set the Parking Brake"
    },
    {
      "text": "Shift an automatic transmission into `Park`, or a manual transmission into first gear or reverse. Turn off the engine and remove the key.",
      "title": "Secure the Transmission"
    },
    {
      "text": "Place a wheel chock against the wheel diagonally opposite the flat tire. If you lack a chock, use a solid block. Confirm it cannot roll or slide.",
      "title": "Chock the Opposite Wheel"
    },
    {
      "text": "Remove the jack, lug wrench, and vehicle owner’s manual from their storage area. Confirm the jack is undamaged and the wrench fits the lug nuts.",
      "title": "Gather the Tire Tools"
    },
    {
      "text": "Check the owner’s manual for the approved jacking point nearest the flat tire. Identify the marked notch, reinforced pinch weld, or frame location shown for your vehicle.",
      "title": "Find the Approved Jack Point"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pull off the wheel cover or center cap if it blocks the lug nuts. Use the tool specified in the owner’s manual to avoid cracking the cover.",
      "title": "Remove the Wheel Cover"
    },
    {
      "text": "Fit the lug wrench fully onto one lug nut and turn it counterclockwise about one-quarter turn. Repeat for every nut in a star pattern; loosen them, but do not remove them yet.",
      "title": "Loosen the Lug Nuts"
    },
    {
      "text": "Place the jack directly under the approved jacking point with its base flat on the ground. Confirm the jack is upright and centered before lifting.",
      "title": "Position the Jack"
    },
    {
      "text": "Operate the jack as shown in the owner’s manual until the flat tire is about 2 inches off the ground. Stop if the jack tilts or the vehicle shifts; never put any part of your body under the vehicle.",
      "title": "Raise the Vehicle"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn each loosened lug nut counterclockwise by hand and remove it. Place the nuts together in the wheel cover or another secure spot so none roll away.",
      "title": "Remove the Lug Nuts"
    },
    {
      "text": "Grip the tire at the 3 and 9 o’clock positions and pull it straight toward you. Keep your feet out from under it; the wheel should slide completely off the hub.",
      "title": "Pull Off the Flat Tire"
    },
    {
      "text": "Lay the removed tire flat beside the vehicle, away from traffic. Confirm the exposed hub is clear and all lug nuts are accounted for; the flat tire is now fully removed.",
      "title": "Secure the Removed Tire"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Gather a French press, kettle, scale, timer, spoon, mug, **30 g coarse coffee grounds**, and at least **500 g water**. You should have everything within reach.",
      "title": "Gather Your Equipment"
    },
    {
      "text": "Heat the water to **93–96°C (200–205°F)**. If you lack a thermometer, bring it to a boil and let it rest for 30 seconds.",
      "title": "Heat the Water"
    },
    {
      "text": "Place a container on the scale and measure **30 g** of coarse coffee grounds. The grounds should resemble coarse sea salt.",
      "title": "Measure the Grounds"
    },
    {
      "text": "Add the measured grounds to the empty French press. Check that the grounds form an even layer at the bottom.",
      "title": "Add the Grounds"
    },
    {
      "text": "Place the French press on the scale and press **Tare**. The display should return to `0 g`.",
      "title": "Tare the Scale"
    },
    {
      "text": "Start a timer set to count upward from `0:00`. Begin the next step immediately.",
      "title": "Start the Timer"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pour hot water evenly over the grounds until the scale reads **500 g**. Make sure all grounds become wet.",
      "title": "Pour the Water"
    },
    {
      "text": "Stir the coffee gently with a spoon for about 5 seconds. No dry grounds should remain on the surface.",
      "title": "Stir the Coffee"
    },
    {
      "text": "Set the lid on the press with the plunger raised above the coffee. The filter should not touch the liquid yet.",
      "title": "Position the Lid"
    },
    {
      "text": "Wait until the timer reaches **4:00**. Keep the French press still while the coffee steeps.",
      "title": "Steep for Four Minutes"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press the plunger straight down slowly for 15–20 seconds. Stop if resistance becomes strong, then continue with gentler pressure.",
      "title": "Plunge Slowly"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pour all the coffee into your mug or a separate carafe immediately. The finished coffee should be clear of most grounds and ready to serve.",
      "title": "Pour the Coffee"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Gather a garden fork, rake, hand trowel, gloves, finished compost, and a soil pH test kit. Keep lime or sulfur available only if the test recommends it.",
      "title": "Gather Your Supplies"
    },
    {
      "text": "Squeeze a handful of soil. Continue if it crumbles when tapped; if it stays in a sticky ball or releases water, wait until the bed dries.",
      "title": "Check the Soil Moisture"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pull all weeds, including their roots, and remove rocks, old roots, and plant debris. The bed should be free of visible obstructions.",
      "title": "Clear the Garden Bed"
    },
    {
      "text": "Use the pH kit according to its package directions. Look for a result between **6.0 and 6.8**, the preferred range for tomatoes.",
      "title": "Test the Soil pH"
    },
    {
      "text": "Apply lime to raise pH or sulfur to lower it only when directed by your test results. Use the package rate for your bed’s measured area.",
      "title": "Adjust the Soil pH"
    },
    {
      "text": "Push a garden fork into the soil and loosen it to a depth of about **12 inches**. Work across the bed until the soil is open and no longer compacted.",
      "title": "Loosen the Soil"
    },
    {
      "text": "Spread **2–3 inches** of finished compost evenly over the bed. The entire surface should have a consistent layer with no bare patches.",
      "title": "Spread the Compost"
    },
    {
      "text": "Blend the compost and any pH amendment into the top **6–8 inches** with the garden fork. The soil should look evenly mixed and crumbly.",
      "title": "Mix in the Amendments"
    },
    {
      "text": "Draw a rake across the bed to break up remaining clods and create an even surface. The finished bed should be level, loose, and free of large lumps.",
      "title": "Rake the Bed Smooth"
    },
    {
      "text": "Water the bed gently until the amended soil is evenly damp but not muddy. Stop when moisture reaches several inches below the surface without puddling.",
      "title": "Moisten the Prepared Bed"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press your hand into the soil and lift it away. The bed is ready when the soil feels loose, holds slight moisture, and leaves no standing water.",
      "title": "Confirm the Bed Is Ready"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Gather the pillowcase pattern, prewashed fabric, measuring tape, fabric scissors, straight pins, and pattern weights. Use fabric scissors only; the blades should cut cleanly without snagging.",
      "title": "Gather Your Tools"
    },
    {
      "text": "Spread the fabric on a large, flat surface and smooth it with the wrong side facing up. The fabric should lie flat without wrinkles, folds, or stretched edges.",
      "title": "Lay Out the Fabric"
    },
    {
      "text": "Measure the fabric’s width and length with the measuring tape. Compare both measurements with the pattern requirements; the fabric must be large enough for every listed piece.",
      "title": "Measure the Fabric"
    },
    {
      "text": "Fold the fabric exactly as directed by the pattern, usually with selvedges together. Align the edges so the fabric lies smooth and the fold has no twists.",
      "title": "Fold the Fabric"
    },
    {
      "text": "Place each pattern piece on the fabric according to the layout diagram. Put any edge labeled **Place on fold** directly against the fabric fold.",
      "title": "Position the Pattern Pieces"
    },
    {
      "text": "Measure from each end of the pattern’s grainline arrow to the nearest selvedge. Adjust the piece until both measurements match, confirming that it is straight.",
      "title": "Align the Grainline"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pin each pattern piece to both fabric layers, placing pins inside the cutting line and parallel to the edges. The paper and fabric should remain flat and secure.",
      "title": "Pin the Pattern"
    },
    {
      "text": "Check that every required pattern piece is pinned and that pieces do not overlap. Confirm that all fold markings and grainline arrows are correctly aligned.",
      "title": "Check the Layout"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cut along each pattern’s outer cutting line using long, smooth scissor strokes. Keep the lower blade against the table and avoid lifting or shifting the fabric.",
      "title": "Cut the Fabric Pieces"
    },
    {
      "text": "Remove the pins and paper one piece at a time, then compare each fabric piece with its pattern. The edges should match the cutting lines with no missing sections.",
      "title": "Verify the Cut Pieces"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Move to a quiet area and hold the guitar in playing position. Keep the tuner, tuner app, or standard-tuning reference pitches within reach.",
      "title": "Set Up in a Quiet Place"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn on the tuner and select **Guitar** or **Chromatic** mode. If using reference pitches, start the standard-tuning audio; you should hear pitches for `E A D G B E`.",
      "title": "Start Your Tuning Source"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the thickest string to low `E` while plucking it repeatedly. Turn its tuning peg slowly until the tuner centers on `E`, or until its pitch matches the reference without wavering.",
      "title": "Tune the Sixth String to E"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the next string to `A` while plucking it repeatedly. Adjust its peg slowly until the tuner centers on `A`, or the string matches the `A` reference pitch.",
      "title": "Tune the Fifth String to A"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the next string to `D` while plucking it repeatedly. Adjust its peg until the tuner centers on `D`, or the string matches the `D` reference pitch.",
      "title": "Tune the Fourth String to D"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the next string to `G` while plucking it repeatedly. Adjust its peg until the tuner centers on `G`, or the string matches the `G` reference pitch.",
      "title": "Tune the Third String to G"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the next string to `B` while plucking it repeatedly. Adjust its peg until the tuner centers on `B`, or the string matches the `B` reference pitch.",
      "title": "Tune the Second String to B"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tune the thinnest string to high `E` while plucking it repeatedly. Adjust its peg until the tuner centers on `E`, or the string matches the higher `E` reference pitch.",
      "title": "Tune the First String to E"
    },
    {
      "text": "Check all strings again from thickest to thinnest: `E A D G B E`. Each tuner reading should center on its target note; correct any string that shifted.",
      "title": "Check Every String Again"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Turn on the camera and check that the battery and memory-card indicators show enough capacity for test photos. If either warning appears, replace or recharge the item before continuing.",
      "title": "Turn On the Camera"
    },
    {
      "text": "Rotate the mode dial to **M** for Manual mode. The display or viewfinder should show `M` with separate ISO, aperture, and shutter-speed values.",
      "title": "Select Manual Mode"
    },
    {
      "text": "Frame the scene through the viewfinder or rear screen. Keep the camera pointed at this composition while evaluating exposure.",
      "title": "Frame Your Scene"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press the ISO button and choose `ISO 100` outdoors in bright light or `ISO 400` indoors. Confirm the selected ISO appears on the display.",
      "title": "Set the ISO"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn the aperture control dial to choose a value such as `f/2.8` for a blurred background or `f/8` for more of the scene in focus. Confirm the chosen f-number appears.",
      "title": "Set the Aperture"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn the shutter-speed dial to at least `1/125` for handheld still subjects or `1/500` for moving subjects. Confirm the speed appears as a fraction or number on the display.",
      "title": "Set the Shutter Speed"
    },
    {
      "text": "Half-press the shutter button to activate the exposure meter. Look for a scale marked `−`, `0`, and `+`; an indicator near `0` suggests balanced exposure.",
      "title": "Read the Exposure Meter"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn the shutter-speed dial until the meter indicator approaches `0`. Use a slower speed if it points toward `−`, or a faster speed if it points toward `+`.",
      "title": "Balance the Meter"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press the shutter button fully to capture a test photo. The image should appear briefly on the rear screen without a recording error.",
      "title": "Take a Test Photo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Open the test photo and enable its histogram using the `Info`, `Display`, or playback options button. A properly exposed image usually has data spread across the graph without piling up heavily at either edge.",
      "title": "Check the Histogram"
    },
    {
      "text": "Adjust ISO upward if the image is too dark or downward if it is too bright. If motion or depth of field matters more, adjust shutter speed or aperture instead. The meter should return near `0`.",
      "title": "Correct the Exposure"
    },
    {
      "text": "Take another photo and review it. Finish when important details are visible, bright areas are not washed out, shadows retain needed detail, and the histogram is not heavily clipped at either edge.",
      "title": "Confirm Proper Exposure"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Stand in a clear space with a mirror to your side, if available. Keep a sturdy chair nearby for balance. You should have enough room to move without touching nearby objects.",
      "title": "Prepare Your Practice Space"
    },
    {
      "text": "Stand tall with your feet about shoulder-width apart and your weight balanced across each whole foot. You should feel your heels, big toes, and little toes pressing into the floor.",
      "title": "Set Your Stance"
    },
    {
      "text": "Turn your toes slightly outward, keeping both feet at similar angles. Your knees should be able to point in the same direction as your toes.",
      "title": "Angle Your Toes Outward"
    },
    {
      "text": "Extend your arms forward at shoulder height. Your arms should remain level and help you balance without pulling your torso forward.",
      "title": "Raise Your Arms"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tighten your abdominal muscles as if preparing for a gentle punch. Keep breathing normally; your torso should feel firm without holding your breath.",
      "title": "Brace Your Core"
    },
    {
      "text": "Lower yourself by moving your hips back and bending your knees together, as if sitting into a chair. Keep your heels planted and your chest facing forward.",
      "title": "Lower Into the Squat"
    },
    {
      "text": "Guide each knee in the same direction as its toes during the descent. In the mirror, your knees should not collapse toward each other.",
      "title": "Track Your Knees"
    },
    {
      "text": "Stop when your thighs are about parallel to the floor, or earlier if your heels lift or you feel pain. Your spine should look neutral rather than rounded.",
      "title": "Check Your Bottom Position"
    },
    {
      "text": "Press through your whole feet to stand, straightening your knees and hips together. Finish tall with your ribs stacked over your hips; do not lean backward.",
      "title": "Stand Back Up"
    },
    {
      "text": "Perform 5 slow repetitions while maintaining planted heels, aligned knees, and a firm torso. Stop if you feel sharp pain; each repetition should look controlled.",
      "title": "Practice Five Repetitions"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Separe `500 g` de farinha de trigo, `240 ml` de água morna, `10 g` de fermento biológico seco, `15 g` de açúcar, `10 g` de sal e `30 ml` de óleo. Use água entre `35 °C` e `40 °C`; ela deve estar morna, não quente.",
      "title": "Separe os ingredientes"
    },
    {
      "text": "Despeje os `240 ml` de água morna em uma tigela pequena. Confirme a temperatura com um termômetro ou toque: a água deve estar confortável, sem queimar.",
      "title": "Coloque a água na tigela"
    },
    {
      "text": "Adicione o fermento e o açúcar à água morna. Mexa apenas até dissolver e deixe a tigela em local sem correntes de ar.",
      "title": "Ative o fermento"
    },
    {
      "text": "Aguarde de `5` a `10` minutos. A mistura deve formar espuma ou bolhas na superfície. Se isso não acontecer, descarte-a e repita com fermento novo e água abaixo de `40 °C`.",
      "title": "Confira a ativação"
    },
    {
      "text": "Coloque a farinha e o sal em uma tigela grande. Misture-os com uma colher até o sal ficar bem distribuído.",
      "title": "Misture os secos"
    },
    {
      "text": "Despeje a mistura de fermento ativado sobre os ingredientes secos. A espuma deve permanecer visível ao entrar na tigela.",
      "title": "Adicione o fermento"
    },
    {
      "text": "Acrescente os `30 ml` de óleo à tigela. Ele deve se espalhar sobre a mistura líquida.",
      "title": "Acrescente o óleo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Mexa com uma colher firme até não restar farinha seca no fundo. A massa ficará irregular e pegajosa; se estiver seca e quebradiça, acrescente água, uma colher de sopa por vez.",
      "title": "Forme a massa"
    },
    {
      "text": "Transfira a massa para uma bancada limpa e levemente enfarinhada. Ela deve sair da tigela como uma única massa, mesmo que ainda esteja pegajosa.",
      "title": "Leve à bancada"
    },
    {
      "text": "Sove por `8` a `10` minutos: empurre a massa com a base da mão, dobre-a sobre si e gire-a. Repita sem acrescentar muita farinha, até ficar lisa e elástica.",
      "title": "Sove a massa"
    },
    {
      "text": "Estique um pequeno pedaço entre os dedos. A massa está pronta quando formar uma película fina sem rasgar imediatamente; se rasgar, sove por mais `2` minutos e teste novamente.",
      "title": "Teste a elasticidade"
    },
    {
      "text": "Modele a massa em uma bola, puxando as bordas para baixo e unindo-as na base. A superfície deve ficar lisa e levemente tensionada, pronta para a primeira fermentação.",
      "title": "Modele a massa"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Reúne una llave ajustable, destornilladores, llave Allen, pinzas, trapo, cubeta y grasa de silicona para plomería. Debes tener todo al alcance antes de desmontar el grifo.",
      "title": "Reúne las herramientas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Coloca una cubeta debajo de las conexiones del grifo. La cubeta debe quedar centrada para recoger cualquier agua residual.",
      "title": "Coloca una cubeta"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cierra las válvulas de agua fría y caliente debajo del lavabo, girándolas a la derecha. Si no existen o no cierran, cierra la llave principal de la vivienda.",
      "title": "Cierra el suministro de agua"
    },
    {
      "text": "Abre el grifo por completo. Continúa cuando deje de salir agua; si el flujo no se detiene, revisa las válvulas antes de desmontarlo.",
      "title": "Libera la presión"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tapa el desagüe con el tapón o un trapo. Comprueba que tornillos y piezas pequeñas no puedan caer dentro.",
      "title": "Tapa el desagüe"
    },
    {
      "text": "Retira la tapa decorativa del mando con un destornillador plano. Busca una pequeña ranura lateral si no se levanta fácilmente.",
      "title": "Retira la tapa del mando"
    },
    {
      "text": "Afloja el tornillo visible con el destornillador o la llave Allen correspondiente. Guárdalo en un recipiente para no perderlo.",
      "title": "Afloja el tornillo del mando"
    },
    {
      "text": "Levanta el mando del grifo en línea recta. Si está atascado, muévelo suavemente de lado a lado sin forzarlo.",
      "title": "Extrae el mando"
    },
    {
      "text": "Desenrosca la cubierta o tuerca que sujeta el mecanismo con la llave ajustable. Protege el acabado con un trapo y gira a la izquierda.",
      "title": "Quita la tuerca de sujeción"
    },
    {
      "text": "Retira el clip de retención con pinzas, si el grifo lo tiene. Déjalo junto a los demás tornillos; el cartucho debe quedar libre.",
      "title": "Retira el clip de retención"
    },
    {
      "text": "Extrae el cartucho o vástago en línea recta. Observa su orientación antes de sacarlo para poder instalar el reemplazo igual.",
      "title": "Extrae el mecanismo interno"
    },
    {
      "text": "Revisa el cartucho, la arandela inferior y los anillos de goma. Busca grietas, deformación, endurecimiento o acumulación mineral que indique daño.",
      "title": "Inspecciona las piezas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Lleva la pieza retirada a una ferretería y compárala con el repuesto. El cartucho, la arandela o los anillos nuevos deben coincidir exactamente en forma y tamaño.",
      "title": "Consigue el repuesto exacto"
    },
    {
      "text": "Limpia el interior del cuerpo del grifo con un trapo húmedo. Retira residuos minerales sin rayar el metal; el asiento debe quedar liso y limpio.",
      "title": "Limpia el alojamiento"
    },
    {
      "text": "Aplica una capa delgada de grasa de silicona para plomería a los anillos de goma nuevos. No uses grasa derivada del petróleo.",
      "title": "Lubrica los sellos nuevos"
    },
    {
      "text": "Inserta el cartucho o vástago nuevo con la misma orientación que tenía la pieza anterior. Debe asentarse por completo sin necesidad de forzarlo.",
      "title": "Instala el mecanismo nuevo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Vuelve a colocar el clip o la tuerca de sujeción. Aprieta solo hasta que el mecanismo quede firme; un exceso puede dañar el repuesto.",
      "title": "Asegura el mecanismo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Coloca el mando sobre el vástago en su posición original. Debe moverse correctamente entre cerrado y abierto.",
      "title": "Coloca el mando"
    },
    {
      "text": "Instala el tornillo y la tapa decorativa del mando. Confirma que el mando quede firme, pero no aprietes demasiado.",
      "title": "Fija el mando"
    },
    {
      "text": "Abre lentamente las válvulas de agua debajo del lavabo girándolas a la izquierda. Detente si aparece una fuga en las conexiones.",
      "title": "Restablece el suministro"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cierra el grifo y observa la salida durante un minuto. La reparación está completa si no cae ninguna gota y no hay humedad alrededor del mando o debajo del lavabo.",
      "title": "Comprueba la reparación"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Press `Ctrl+S` on Windows or `Command+S` on Mac. If the document has not been saved before, a Save or Save As window will open.",
      "title": "Start Saving"
    },
    {
      "text": "Select the folder where you want to keep the document. The selected folder should appear as the current save location.",
      "title": "Choose a Save Location"
    },
    {
      "text": "Click the **File name** or **Save As** field and type a clear name for the document. Keep the suggested file extension, such as `.docx`.",
